text:
I've tested hundreds of AI tools over the last year

These are the ones I'd genuinely recommend 👇                                                                                                                                                                                                      

Research and Discovery

@perplexity_ai AI answer engine with real-time web sources
@ManusAI Agent built for multi-step workflows and execution
@adeptailabs Enterprise AI for workflow automation
@MerlinAIByFoyer Browser copilot for research and summaries
@OpenAI ChatGPT for writing, coding, images and voice
@AnthropicAI Claude for analysis, reasoning and long-form work

Build and Ship

@Lovable Turn ideas into apps using prompts
@emergentlabs Designs, builds and deploys from chat
@cursor_ai AI-native coding environment
@Replit Cloud development with AI agents
@cognition Autonomous AI engineer

Design and Creative

@magnific Image enhancement and creative workflows
@GammaApp AI presentations, websites and docs
@midjourney AI image generation
@canva Design suite with built-in AI features

Video and Content

@Kling_ai AI-generated videos from text and images
@arcads_ai UGC-style ad creation
@OpusClip Long-form content into short clips
@descript Transcript-based editing
@capcutapp AI editing, captions and templates
@tavus Personalized AI avatars

Audio and Meetings

@ElevenLabs Voice generation and dubbing
@retellai AI voice agents
@PLAUDAI Smart recorder for notes and transcripts
@ReadAI_ Meeting and email copilot
@otter_ai Meeting notes and summaries
@happy_scribe Transcription and translation

Growth and Operations

@ClayRunHQ Data enrichment and GTM automation
@11x_official AI-powered digital workers
@InstantlyAI Outreach and cold email automation
@MetaviewAI Interview and hiring assistant
@CustomerIO Customer engagement automation
@micro1_ai Human data platform for AI systems

Productivity

@NotionHQ Notes, docs and knowledge management
@Superhuman AI-first email workflow
@cluely Real-time AI assistant
@useMotion AI scheduling and planning
@glean Enterprise search assistant
@fyxerofficial AI email assistant

AI moves so fast that knowing the right tools is becoming a skill of its own

Anything you would add to that list?
